3 ARTICLE 5
4 MONEY TRANSMISSION LICENSES
5 Sec. 21. (1) A person may not engage in the business of money
6 transmission or advertise, solicit, or hold itself out as providing
7 money transmission unless the person is licensed under this act.
8 (2) Subsection (1) does not apply to either of the following:
9 (a) A person that is an authorized delegate of a person
10 licensed under this act acting within the scope of authority
11 conferred by a written contract with the licensee.
12 (b) A person that is exempt under section 7 and does not
13 engage in money transmission outside the scope of such exemption.
14 (3) A license issued under section 29 is not transferable or
15 assignable.
16 Sec. 23. (1) To establish consistent licensing between
17 Michigan and other states, the director is authorized to do either
18 or both of the following:
19 (a) Implement all licensing provisions of this act in a manner
20 that is consistent with other states that have adopted this act or
21 multistate licensing processes.
22 (b) Participate in nationwide protocols for licensing
23 cooperation and coordination among state regulators provided that
24 such protocols are consistent with this act.
25 (2) In order to fulfill the purposes of this act, the director
26 is authorized to establish relationships or contracts with the
27 nationwide multistate licensing system and registry or other
28 entities designated by the nationwide multistate licensing system
29 and registry to enable the director to do any of the following:
WAM H02309'25 (H-2) tvg6xh

