1 TIMELY TRANSMISSION, REFUNDS, AND DISCLOSURES
2 Sec. 55. (1) Every licensee shall forward all money received
3 for transmission in accordance with the terms of the agreement
4 between the licensee and the sender unless the licensee has a
5 reasonable belief or a reasonable basis to believe that the sender
6 may be a victim of fraud or that a crime or violation of law, rule,
7 or regulation has occurred, is occurring, or may occur.
8 (2) If a licensee fails to forward money received for
9 transmission in accordance with this section, the licensee shall
10 respond to inquiries by the sender with the reason for the failure
11 unless providing a response would violate a state or federal law,
12 rule, or regulation.
13 Sec. 57. (1) This section does not apply to either of the
14 following:
15 (a) Money received for transmission subject to 12 CFR 1005.30
16 to 1005.36.
17 (b) Money received for transmission under a written agreement
18 between the licensee and payee to process payments for goods or
19 services provided by the payee.
20 (2) Every licensee shall refund to the sender within 10 days
21 of receipt of the sender's written request for a refund of any and
22 all money received for transmission unless any of the following
23 occurs:
24 (a) The money has been forwarded within 10 days of the date on
25 which the money was received for transmission.
26 (b) Instructions have been given committing an equivalent
27 amount of money to the person designated by the sender within 10
28 days of the date on which the money was received for transmission.
29 (c) The agreement between the licensee and the sender
WAM H02309'25 (H-2) tvg6xh

41
1 instructs the licensee to forward the money at a time that is
2 beyond 10 days of the date on which the money was received for
3 transmission. If funds have not yet been forwarded in accordance
4 with the terms of the agreement between the licensee and the
5 sender, the licensee shall issue a refund in accordance with the
6 other provisions of this section.
7 (d) The refund is requested for a transaction that the
8 licensee has not completed based on a reasonable belief or a
9 reasonable basis to believe that a crime or violation of law, rule,
10 or regulation has occurred, is occurring, or may occur.
11 (e) The refund request does not enable the licensee to do
12 either of the following:
13 (i) Identify the sender's name and address or telephone number.
14 (ii) Identify the particular transaction to be refunded in the
15 event the sender has multiple transactions outstanding.
16 Sec. 59. (1) Every licensee or its authorized delegate shall
17 provide the sender a receipt for money received for transmission.
18 The receipt must contain the name of the sender, the name of the
19 designated recipient, the date of the transaction, the unique
20 transaction or identification number, the name of the licensee, the
21 nationwide multistate licensing system and registry unique ID, the
22 licensee's business address, and the licensee's customer service
23 telephone number, the amount of the transaction in United States
24 dollars, any fee charged by the licensee to the sender for the
25 transaction, and any taxes collected by the licensee from the
26 sender for the transaction. The receipt required by this subsection
27 must be in English and in the language principally used by the
28 licensee or authorized delegate to advertise, solicit, or
29 negotiate, either orally or in writing, for a transaction conducted
WAM H02309'25 (H-2) tvg6xh

42
1 in person, electronically or by phone, if other than English.
2 (2) This section does not apply to any of the following:
3 (a) Money received for transmission subject to 12 CFR 1005.30
4 to 1005.36.
5 (b) Money received for transmission that is not primarily for
6 personal, family, or household purposes.
7 (c) Money received for transmission under a written agreement
8 between the licensee and the payee to process payments for goods or
9 services provided by the payee.
10 (d) Payroll processing services.
11 (3) As used in this section, "receipt" means a paper receipt,
12 electronic record, or other written confirmation. For a transaction
13 conducted in person, the receipt may be provided electronically if
14 the sender requests or agrees to receive an electronic receipt. For
15 a transaction conducted electronically or by phone, a receipt may
