4 Sec. 81. (1) A person that intentionally makes a false
5 statement, misrepresentation, or false certification in any record
6 or document filed or required to be maintained under this act or
7 that intentionally makes a false entry or omits a material entry in
8 a record is guilty of a felony punishable by imprisonment for not
9 more than 5 years or a fine of not more than $100,000.00, or both.
10 (2) A person that engages in criminal fraud in the conduct of
11 its money transmission services business is guilty of a felony
12 punishable by imprisonment for not more than 5 years or a fine of
13 not more than $100,000.00, or both.
14 (3) A person that knowingly engages in an activity for which a
15 license is required under this act and is not licensed under this
16 act is guilty of a felony punishable by imprisonment for not more
17 than 5 years or a fine of not more than $100,000.00, or both. A
18 court shall order a person convicted of violating subsection (1) or
19 (2) to pay restitution as provided in section 1a of chapter IX of
20 the code of criminal procedure, 1927 PA 175, MCL 769.1a, and the
21 William Van Regenmorter crime victim's rights act, 1985 PA 87, MCL
22 780.751 to 780.834.
23 Sec. 83. The director may assess a civil fine against a person
24 that violates this act or a rule adopted or an order issued under
25 this act in an amount not to exceed $10,000.00 per day for each day
26 the violation is outstanding, plus this state's costs and expenses
27 for the investigation and prosecution of the matter, including
28 reasonable attorney fees.
